Hong Kong and mainland Chinese stocks ended the week on a positive note Friday as investors cheered news that China and the US would resume trade talks next month. The Hang Seng Index climbed 0.66% to 26 690.76, finishing the week more than 3% higher. The benchmark Shanghai Composite Index gained 0.46% to 2 999.60 - it rose 3.9% this week. The Shenzhen Composite Index, which tracks stocks on China's second exchange, added 0.36% to 1 657.50, gaining five percent since last Friday. 